excerpt: Hello! I'm Meatball, a 13 year-old tabby cat. My interests include being handsome, soft surfaces, cheese, sitting in the window to keep watch over the alley behind my home, letting bugs live, staring, yelling at my human to get out of the shower, making friends with almost everyone I meet, and be...
description:
HI EVERYONE

It’s been a minute!

I am:

1) not dead
2) still pissed that Loki is
3) sorry I haven’t updated in so long

Since last fall my family and I have been hit with one challenge after another. My mom was diagnosed with a terminal lung disease, I got into a nasty bike wreck (I’m OK now!), my best friend will soon undergo two major surgeries, and last week I found out that my beloved 13 year-old cat, Meatball, has been diagnosed with large cell lymphoma. He will begin chemotherapy on March 29th.

I hate asking people for anything, ever, but my friend made me set up a GoFundMe and I would do anything for Meatball, so I’m swallowing my pride and sharing the link for anyone who may be able to donate. He means the world to me and I want to do everything I can to give him the best quality of life for as long as possible. He deserves it.

Sorry to get serious and go OT on this super frivolous side blog, but there are some really awesome pockets of the Marvel fandom and I figured there could be some cat-lovers who may want to help out. Any donation amount is appreciated, and shares/reblogs are appreciated as well. I’ll be posting updates to the GFM page about Meatball’s progress, if anyone would like to follow along. He’s a very special creature, and now that I know what flerkens are I’m pretty sure he is one.

Thanks so much for any and all support, and once things have calmed down a little bit I’ll be back on here to weep and rage against whatever happens to our faves in Endgame. Hope you’re all well and thriving!

summary: i just got back from watching Captain Marvel and Yep! that’s gay that montage of Carol falling and getting back on her feet at...
body:
i just got back from watching Captain Marvel and

  • Yep! that’s gay
  • that montage of Carol falling and getting back on her feet at various points in her life + her finally getting her full powers in the present was as satisfying as WW’s No Man’s Land scene. i said what i said
  • so many 90s classics on that soundtrack! but i kinda wish they had set the movie a couple years later so they could use that one Chumbawamba song as well
